>, a borrowing of Old Norse <i>greifi</i> ‘earl, count’ (see   Grave  ). In Durham and Northumberland the source is Middle English <i>greve</i>, from Old (Northumbrian) English <i>grǣfa</i> with the same meaning (see   Grieve  ).","English: possibly a habitational name from Greysouthen (Cumbria), recorded as <i>Graysone</i> in 1505."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Garisie de Gaveston was born about 1230, in Béarn, France as the son of Bernard De Gabeston. He had at least 1 son. He died after 1230, in his hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1230–after 1230":"umbes 1230–pärast 1230","1230–1230":"1230–1230","1247–1302":"1247–1302","1210–1210":"1210–1210","Abt 1230":"umbes 1230","1302":"1302","1247":"1247","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","after 1230":"pärast 1230","Gabeston, Bearn, Basse-Pyrennes, France":"Béarn, Prantsusmaa","Béarn, France":"Béarn, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1230–after 1230":"noin 1230–1230 jälkeen","1230–1230":"1230–1230","1247–1302":"1247–1302","1210–1210":"1210–1210","Abt 1230":"noin 1230","1302":"1302","1247":"1247","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","after 1230":"1230 jälkeen","Gabeston, Bearn, Basse-Pyrennes, France":"Béarn, Ranska","Béarn, France":"Béarn, Ranska"},"fr":{"Abt 1230–after 1230":"environ 1230–après 1230","1230–1230":"1230–1230","1247–1302":"1247–1302","1210–1210":"1210–1210","Abt 1230":"environ 1230","1302":"1302","1247":"1247","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","after 1230":"après 1230","Gabeston, Bearn, Basse-Pyrennes, France":"Béarn, France","Béarn, France":"Béarn, France","lifeSummary":"Garisie de Gaveston est né environ 1230, à Béarn, France, fils de Bernard De Gabeston. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé après 1230, dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"Abt 1230–after 1230":"um 1230–nach 1230","1230–1230":"1230–1230","1247–1302":"1247–1302","1210–1210":"1210–1210","Abt 1230":"um 1230","1302":"1302","1247":"124